cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the impact of cellular network design on machine learning inference accuracy, which involves both networking and machine learning concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an analytical framework to characterize inference accuracy, which involves statistical and mathematical modeling, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the impact of bandwidth and reliability on inference accuracy, which involves information theory and communication engineering concepts, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. The paper also discusses the coordination between edge devices and remote compute nodes, which involves control and system engineering concepts, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the proliferation of smart wireless devices leveraging ML inference, which involves multimedia and human-computer interaction concepts, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
